    {
      "id": "f1441a0129d5b01ae40b9cd711027f49ea3d3db3",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 131,
        "name": "Jian Yu",
        "email": "yujian@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "yujian"
      },
      "date": "2011-12-19 15:35:11.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> Instead of hard coding the maximum xattr size into all of the tests it should be a constant set by large_xattr_enabled(). Maybe instead of returning a Boolean true/false value it should be renamed large_xattr_size() and return the maximum xattr size?\n\nI added a new function max_xattr_size() to return the maximum xattr size. Since the current large xattr implementation could save a full 65536 bytes value in an external inode, I made that function still return 65536 while large xattr feature enabled. After \"mid-sized\" xattr support is implemented, I'd revise the function.\n\n> The other issue is that these tests _could_ test the large xattr support, but do not. If they are left disabled then it is unlikely that they will ever be enabled. At a minimum, once the ldiskfs patch lands some conf-sanity test should format a small large_ filesystem and always test this feature.\n\nI added conf-sanity test 61 for this. There are some basic operations in the test (save, shrink, grow, check after remount, remove). It's not a full test set. Should I add more tests like what xfstests #020 and #062 do as follows?\n\n#020:\n\n\"*** list non-existant file\"\n\"*** list empty file\"\n\"*** query non-existant attribute\"\n\"*** one attribute\"\n\"*** replace attribute\"\n\"*** add attribute\"\n\"*** remove attribute\"\n\"*** add lots of attributes\"\n\"*** check\"\n\"*** remove lots of attributes\"\n\"*** really long value\"\n\"*** set/get/remove really long names (expect failure)\"\n\"*** check final\"\n\"*** delete\"\n\n#062:\n\n\"*** set/get one initially empty attribute\"\n\"*** overwrite empty, set several new attributes\"\n\"*** fetch several attribute names and values (hex)\"\n\"*** fetch several attribute names and values (base64)\"\n\"*** shrink value of an existing attribute\"\n\"*** grow value of existing attribute\"\n\"*** set an empty value for second attribute\"\n\"*** overwrite empty value\"\n\"*** remove attribute\"\n\"*** final list (strings, type=$inode, nsp=$nsp)\"\n\"*** directory descent with us following symlinks\"\n\"*** directory descent without following symlinks\"\n\"*** backup everything\"\n\"*** clear out the scratch device\"\n\"*** reset test bed with no extended attributes\"\n\"*** restore everything\"\n\"*** compare before and after backups\"",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
