        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2011-12-26 05:07:40.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\nThere are two ways to address this I think. Either this patch is rebased on the ldiskfs patch, or the test can check if the MDS filesystem has large xattr support or is skipped otherwise. \n\nNormally I would say to make the test check this for allowing interop testing, but for conf sanity where the test is formatted locally it shouldn't be affected by interop so rebasing this patch should be enough.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 5
    },
